Frederick Bristol Buckingham (February 13, 1876 â€“ December 3, 1948) was a Major League Baseball pitcher. Buckingham played for the Washington Senators in the 1895 season. He played just one game in his career, pitching in 3 innings, with a 6.00 ERA.
Buckingham attended Yale University.
Buckingham was born in Blenheim, New York and died in Washington, D.C.
